'''''The Dancers''''' is a 1930 American [[Pre-Code Hollywood|Pre-Code]] melodrama, produced and distributed by [[Fox Film Corporation]], and directed by Chandler Sprague.<ref>[http://www.afi.com/members/catalog/AbbrView.aspx?s=&Movie=3560 ''The Dancers'' Detail View], AFI.com; accessed August 9, 2015.</ref> It is based on a 1923 Broadway play by [[Viola Tree]] and [[Gerald du Maurier]].<ref>[http://ibdb.com/production.php?id=9294 ''The Dancers'' details], ibdb.com; accessed August 9, 2015.</ref> The film marks the feature sound film debut of actress [[Mrs. Patrick Campbell]]. The setting was shifted from the play's [[South America]] to [[Canada]].

==Cast==
*[[Lois Moran]] - Diana
*[[Phillips Holmes]] - Tony
*[[Walter Byron (actor)|Walter Byron]] - Berwin
*[[Mae Clarke]] - Maxine
*[[Tyrell Davis]] - Archie
*[[Mrs. Patrick Campbell]] - Aunt Emily

